= Kernel Documentation
:toc: left
:icons: font
:sectlinks:

See also: link:../index.html[Home], link:../devel.html[Developer Guide], link:../roadmap.html[Roadmap]

This section documents the Valecium kernel implementation by subsystem. Each page below corresponds to a directory under `kernel/` in the source tree and provides a brief overview of responsibilities and key components.

== Kernel Subsystems

* link:arch.html[arch.ad] — Architecture-specific boot, CPU, and memory implementations (i686 only)
* link:cpu.html[cpu.ad] — Process model, scheduler, fork/exec
* link:drivers.html[drivers.ad] — Hardware device drivers (ATA, FDC, keyboard, TTY)
* link:fs.html[fs.ad] — Filesystem stack (VFS, FAT12/16/32, devfs, disk/partition abstractions)
* link:hal.html[hal.ad] — Hardware abstraction layer interface and operation tables
* link:init.html[init.ad] — Kernel startup flow and handoff logic
* link:mem.html[mem.ad] — PMM, VMM, kernel heap, process heap, stack management
* link:signal.html[signal.ad] — Signal handling infrastructure (in progress)
* link:std.html[std.ad] — Kernel-local libc-style utility implementations
* link:sys.html[sys.ad] — System services, ELF loader, command line, kernel modules
* link:syscall.html[syscall.ad] — Syscall dispatch and handlers
* link:crypto.html[crypto.ad] — Cryptographic algorithm implementations (MD5, SHA1)

== Navigation Notes

* Start with link:init.html[init.ad] for boot order and subsystem initialization sequence.
* Read link:hal.html[hal.ad] and link:arch.html[arch.ad] together to understand portability boundaries.
* Link this section with link:../usr/index.html[Userspace Documentation] to follow kernel ↔ userspace interactions.

